title: For Sale:  Madsen model 1947 Rifle
postcontent: RIFLE:  Madsen Model 1947CALIBER:  .30-06LENGTHY:  1080 mmBARREL LENGTH:  595 mmWEIGHT:  3.65 kg emptyMAGAZINE CAPACITY:  5 roundsCOUNTRY OF ORIGIN:  DenmarkThis rifle is a very unique piece to begin with, but this particular one is exceptional in that it has never been fired.  The Madsen model 1947 rifle, also known as "the Madsen Lightweight Military Rifle" or "Columbian Navy M1958 rifle", was designed and manufactured by Dansk Industrie Sindikat Madsen A.S., mostly to be offered to third world countries whose armies had not enough funds to buy and maintain semi- or full-automatic infantry rifles.  This rifle was first offered in DISA/Madsen catalogs in 1947, but initially found no buyers as world arms markets were flooded with surplus rifles of the WWII era, and the focus of military interest had shifted from bolt action rifles towards semi-automatic and automatic rifles.  In 1958 the Columbian Navy made an order for Madsen Model 1947 rifles in caliber .30-06 US, but it appears that most of them were never issued but were sold as surplus almost immediately upon receipt.  The total production of the Madsen model 1947 rifle is estimated at around 5-6 thousand rifles.  The Madsen model 1947 rifle is often called the last military bolt action rifle, as it was designed and manufactured when bolt-action rifles finally became obsolete as standard military issue rifles.The Madsen model 1947 rifle is a manually operated bolt action rifle.  It uses rotary bolt action with dual locking lugs, located at the rear of the bolt body.  Bolt lugs engage cuts, made on the inner receiver walls just behind the magazine housing.  The cocking handle is located at the middle of the bolt and bent down for more comfortable carry.  A manual safety is located at the rear of the bolt, and has two positions.  The rifle is fed from an integral, non-detachable box magazine that holds 5 rounds.  The magazine is reloaded from the top when the bolt is opened.  Sighting equipment consists of a protected front sight and an aperture type rear sight, which is adjustable for windage and elevation between 100 and 900 meters.  To decrease felt recoil of the rifle, it is equipped with an internal muzzle brake and a rubber buttplate.These rifles are quite rare, and in unfired condition such as this one, almost unobtainable.  The price is firm and not negotiable.  Shipping, if required, is solely the responsibility of the buyer.  If you have any questions or would like to see more photos of the rifle, please let me know
